{
  "stem": "27507.8",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the cellar.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, and there were-- we were actually were already then that the war is going on, because the Soviets were occasionally bombarding, bombing, Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one occasion that I remember, that must have been end of August or early September, that my father, and I, and an aunt, we were all locked in the office in the factory on the third floor, and locked by my uncle, because that was supposed to be a safer place in case the Germans would come in the night.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the horrible bombardment started by the Soviets, by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we were on the third floor of the factory, in the large industrial complex, which was not the best place to be during the bombardment.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was very-- and we couldn't get out, because the door was locked.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The window was covered with a iron grill.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was a complete trap.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But even then, one was somehow had a feeling of certain elation when one knew that the Soviets are bombing, that there is an air bombardment by the Soviets, because one felt that there is still somebody who is actually fighting the Germans, which for us it almost seemed as if the rest of the world didn't exist anymore, that everything was-- it was if the war was-- we didn't feel that the war was still going on.",
      "word_count": 78
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the action was going on in this way until the 6th of September.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And on the 6th of September--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'42, it was all '42.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was all a business of six weeks, approximately, since the later part of July.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in September, suddenly, things were happening all the time suddenly, without any-- obviously, it's a surprise, horrible surprise.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, suddenly, there was an announcement.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
